Description: Heavily corroded fragment of a copper alloy implement in the shape of a flat and slightly curved prong, splaying on each side of a round hole at the broken end. In spite of the shape, the item looks too thick to be the blade of a knife.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.77, p.185, pl.27)
Condition: poor, corroded, broken in three pieces reunited
